About the Project Olympic Dam Mine, operated by BHP-one of the world\'s
largest mining companies-is located approximately 550 km north‑west of
Adelaide and produces copper, gold and uranium.\
\
As one of the largest contractors on site, this opportunity offers
valuable experience to support the growth of your maintenance career
within underground mining.\
\
The Role This position operates on a **2 & 2 roster**, working **12‑hour
shifts**, and is responsible for leading maintenance activities across
underground and surface operations.\
\
Key responsibilities include:

-   Leading and supervising a team of maintenance technicians, providing
    guidance, support and mentorship

-   Ensuring all site and workshop activities comply with health,
    safety, training, environmental and statutory requirements

-   Managing and conducting personal risk assessments and Job Safety
    Analyses (JSAs) to maintain safety awareness and compliance

-   Conducting preventative maintenance inspections to identify and
    address potential issues proactively

-   Overseeing maintenance execution to ensure compliance with quality
    standards

-   Assigning tasks effectively to optimise resource utilisation

-   Maintaining accurate maintenance records, including work orders,
    daily reports and equipment history

-   Managing and reviewing inventory of spare parts, tooling and
    equipment required for maintenance activities

About You To be successful in this role, you will have:

-   Heavy Duty Diesel Fitter/Mechanic trade qualifications

-   Demonstrated experience in a Supervisor role working with
    underground and heavy‑duty equipment

-   Proficiency with Computerised Maintenance Management Systems (CMMS)

-   Strong planning and organisational skills

-   A high level of initiative with the ability to perform under
    pressure

-   Strong leadership capability and well‑rounded communication skills

-   A valid manual driver\'s licence

-   A positive work ethic aligned with Redpath\'s motto: **\"Consider it
    done - safely.\"**

What We Offer In return, you can expect:

-   Clear career pathways and opportunities for internal promotion

-   Competitive hourly rates + super paid on all hours

-   Even time roster for true work life balance

-   Ongoing training & OEM accredited trade courses

-   Clear career progression pathways

-   All PPE provided

-   High‑quality camp facilities, including ensuite rooms, gym, pool and
    wet mess

-   Telstra and Optus coverage onsite

-   Salary sacrifice options for superannuation and novated car leasing

-   Discounted private health insurance through BUPA

-   Prescription safety glasses reimbursement (up to \$200)

-   Employee Assistance Program (4 sessions per annum), with wellbeing
    support available for the whole family

-   Redzone Reward Program - discounts and cashback at hundreds of
    retailers

-   Service milestone Bonuses:

    -   \$3k at 5 years

